Tell Me a Story--One of our scholarship donors is offering two $2500 scholarships to seniors with a knack for storytelling. The story should be about yourself and your life, and must be told orally. You must submit an audio file in order to be considered. Please be advised, the donor requests to hear the two winning entries, which means one or more people outside of our school community may hear the story. Stories may be submitted here:
https://drive.google.com/open?id=1mS7bRGrnPmTubz_G3JJpmttE0kATK_hm
This scholarship is only open to West Haven High School Students, which means both recipients will be selected from our senior class. The check for $2500 is given directly to you, to be used as you choose for your pursuits after high school. Entries are due THIS TUESDAY BY MIDNIGHT!!

post_text:
Cap and Gown info--WHHS Senior Parents,
Pickup for cap and gowns will take place on June 4th at West Haven High School. Cords for those who have earned them will also be handed out. We ask that parents follow the schedule below to avoid traffic issues.
Last Names A-F (in vehicle) 9:00 AM until 10:00 AM
Last Names G-N (in vehicle) 10:00 AM until 11:00 AM
Last Names O-Z (in vehicle) 11:00 AM until Noon
Walkers- 12:30 until 1 PM
We ask that students write their last name large and legibly on a piece of paper to hold up to the car window. We can then notify those pulling the packages for hand out that you will be coming down the line as we anticipate heavy car traffic. This will also minimize contact. In the interest of pedestrian safety, we ask that 12:30 until 1 PM be reserved for those without vehicles.

post_text: The Connecticut Supreme Courtâ€™s Historical Society sponsored essay and art competitions for local high school students on various important legal principles. The programs have explored topics such as the separation of powers doctrine, the rights afforded by Miranda v. Arizona, and a keynote lecture on the "Magna Carta: Symbol of Freedom Under Law." This yearâ€™s essay award recipient is Christopher Dâ€™Inezo, an AP U.S. Government and Politics student at West Haven High School. All students are safe in the rink and the pool. There is no danger to students. There is a large police presence near Platt Avenue that is UNRELATED to the evacuation at WHHS.
